<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Character homes, city views and one of Brisbane's best village strips.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Paddington is one of Brisbane's most recognisable inner-west suburbs. Its steep streets, Federation cottages and elevated city views attract buyers who are looking for genuine character in a location that is genuinely convenient. At under 4 kilometres from the CBD, it offers walkability that most inner suburbs cannot match.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I work with buyers and sellers right across Brisbane's inner west. I understand what Paddington buyers are chasing and how to position a home to generate real competition. Whether your property is a renovated Queenslander with city views or an unrenovated cottage with strong bones, the approach needs to match the buyer profile.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The Latrobe Terrace café strip anchors the suburb's lifestyle appeal and is a genuine drawcard for buyers relocating from interstate or from apartment living who want that walkable village feel. Proximity to the Royal Brisbane and Women's Hospital and QUT Kelvin Grove campus supports consistent demand from professionals and academic staff. Homes on elevated streets with north-facing aspects and city or ranges views consistently outperform comparable lower-lying properties. The renovation market here is active: owner-occupiers compete hard for original-condition homes with scope to add value, and that competition benefits sellers who price correctly.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Paddington Specialist</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Inner West Brisbane</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Character Home Market</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Strong renovator and owner-occupier demand</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:#78716c;margin-top:2rem;">Also selling in: <a href="/suburbs/red-hill" style="color:#c4912a;">Red Hill</a>, <a href="/suburbs/bardon" style="color:#c4912a;">Bardon</a>, <a href="/suburbs/west-end" style="color:#c4912a;">West End</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
     SECTION: FAQ
════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">FAQ</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Common questions about Paddington.</h2>
    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the median house price in Paddington Brisbane?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Paddington's median sits in a strong range driven by demand for character homes in an inner-west location. Pricing varies considerably depending on block size, renovation quality and whether the property carries city or ranges views. An appraisal will give you a precise read on where your home sits relative to current sales.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Paddington?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-presented Paddington homes typically sell within 25 to 40 days. Buyer demand in this pocket remains consistent given the suburb's walkability, the Latrobe Terrace café strip, and limited supply of genuine character homes within a short commute of the CBD.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Paddington Brisbane?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Paddington has one of Brisbane's most distinct inner-city lifestyles. The Latrobe Terrace strip is walkable, genuinely local and well-established. Steep streets carry city views on clear days, and the suburb's Federation and Queenslander homes give it a visual identity buyers find hard to replicate elsewhere at the same price point.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What types of homes are in Paddington?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Paddington is predominantly character housing: Federation cottages, traditional Queenslanders and inter-war homes. Many have been renovated with modern interiors while retaining original facades, which is what buyers consistently seek here. Unrenovated properties also attract strong interest from owner-occupier renovators who are willing to pay well for the right bones.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

